What is Nuku?
\f1\b0 \cf0 \
Nuku is a personal Japanese tutor, teaching you the two native Japanese writing systems, hiragana and katakana. It features both these systems, all three main romanization systems and methods of selecting what to learn. It was written to aid me in my Japanese studies.\
\

\f0\b \cf2 What are romanization systems?
\f1\b0 \cf0 \
There are several methods of romanizing Japanese - that is, turning the Japanese into roman characters. The three main ones are Hepburn, Kunreisiki and Nihonsiki. \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
The official system is Kunreisiki. Another, Hepburn, was designed to romanize according to pronounciation, rather than a fixed table. Nihonsiki is similar to Kunreisiki.\
