\f0\b \cf2 What is hiragana? And what about this katakana thing?
\f1\b0 \cf0 \
Hiragana and katakana, or collectively 
\f2\i kana
\f1\i0 , are two of the writing systems in Japanese, the third then being kanji. Kana are much more like our alphabet than kanji is though, as there are only about 70 unique characters - there are several thousand kanji.\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Kana is the first thing a Japanese learns in school, and every word can be written using them. However, normally a mix of hiragana and kanji is used. Katakana is similar to hiragana but looks different. It is used instead of the latter, when writing foreign words, or for extra emphasis.\
